post_text: Good Morning: With the uptick in positive cases we are moving from tier 2 to tier 3. The difference in tier 2 and tier 3 is that we will ask students to wear masks on the buses, in the hallways, and when social distancing isn't possible. Other changes that may happen: students stay in rooms and teachers move, student entrance for the school day, and lunch (in classrooms). If you have any questions, please email Eric.Knight@k12.sd.us Thanks

post_text:
Yesterday, will walked back into the classroom for the first time since leaving school abruptly on March 13, 2020 due to the coronavirus. Students ended the year in a remote learning environment, missing out on important face-to-face instruction and relationships with teachers and friends.

As students and staff return to school this fall, they will bring their collective experiences with them and make a fresh start.

As we prepare to greet them, we are asking our entire community to come together to support our staff and our students with the message that no matter the learning space - we are ALL in this ‚Äútogether.‚Äù Hang a royal blue ribbon in your window. Write ‚Äútogether‚Äù in window paint. Decorate your home and office to show support. Let staff and students know you‚Äôre standing by them. You care about them. You wish them success.

We know school won‚Äôt look and feel exactly the same this year.
But, school is still school ‚Äì a place where hope and possibility meet for a bright future.
We are better ‚Äútogether.‚Äù

shared_text:
Centerville Tornadoes Track and Field
May 27 at 5:50 PM ¬∑

With the summer kicking off we would like to provide kids with workouts to do in the off season. This is totally voluntary for those seeking self improvement. The workouts won't be one size fits all and will be tailored for sprinters and mid to long distance runners. Parents are more than welcome to participate as well if they're motivated to take on a workout plan. It will include classic well known body weight workouts of the day (WODs) that everyone can do with no equipment and will also include running. For the running, we would like everyone with a smartphone to download the Strava app, which will allow them to record their route, pace, and overall achievements. Strava is also a social media app, so they can follow the achievements of the rest of the team as we go. After downloading the app, they will have to create a strava profile and join the Centerville Track and Field Club which can be found under the clubs tab on the Strava App. We will begin posting workouts tomorrow.

post_text:
Each month the NHS students choose a staff member of the Centerville School District for "Educator of the Month," for the previous month. Educators are chosen for their commitment to scholarship, leadership, service, and character.

Below is a picture of NHS members Sophie Eide, Haley Meyer, Tori Herrboldt, Blake Johnson, and Mya Bendt presenting the virtual certificate to Dr. Kelly Dilliard (May) and Mrs. Jamey Strom (April) (not pictured: Megan Stevens, Hunter Ellis, and Alyssa Brandsrud).

Congratulations to Mrs. Strom (April) and Dr. Dilliard (May) for being chosen by the NHS to be Educator of the Month!
We appreciate all the time, effort, and contributions that they have made to the Centerville School District.

SDFFAFOUNDATION.ORG
South Dakota FFA Foundation, Inc.

Jessie Knutson shared a link to the group: Centerville FFA.
May 7 at 12:48 PM ¬∑

State FFA Degrees Awarded-

Blake Johnson will be awarded his State FFA Degree during this virtual ceremony.

The State FFA Degree is the highest degree of membership conferred by the South Dakota FFA Association. The requirements for this degree include:

‚óè Having earned and productively invested at least $1,000, or worked at least 300 hours in excess of scheduled class time, or a combination thereof, in a Supervised Agricultural Experience program.

‚óè Demonstrated leadership ability by performing ten procedures of Parliamentary Law, giving a six-minute speech on an agriculture or FFA-related topic and serving as an officer, committee chairperson or participating member of a chapter committee.

‚óè Have completed at least 25 hours of community service.

282 South Dakota FFA members will be recognized for receiving their State FFA Degree at the 92nd South Dakota State FFA Convention, broadcast virtually, Wednesday, May 13, 2020, at 7:00pm

We hope to see our smiling kids tonight.
